{
  "texts": [
    "The adaptive sparse self-attention network was designed to anticipate fine-grained performance and to generate missing data.",
    "The feature's matrix representation enables position-wise feature selection, making it easier to identify the elements from the previous learning stage that are most associated, which results in embedding of the original features and their spatial associations.",
    "To achieve sequence generation, a DNN model was built with several of sparse self-attention layers placed on top of one another.",
    "An experiment using three datasets from various e-learning platforms demonstrated the benefits and effectiveness of the proposed model.",
    "To determine whether transfer learning expedites training and enhances performance using the potential of DNNs, Tsiakmaki et al (2020) suggested an approach for predicting student performance."
  ]
}